maAxiDN, applied to a she-camel, (ISh, IAạr, Ṣ, Ḳ,) and to a woman, and a ewe or she-goat, (IAạr, Mṣb, Ḳ,) and any pregnant animal, (Ṣ, A,* Mṣb,) ‡ Taken with the pains of parturition, (ISh, IAạr, Ṣ, A, Mṣb,) being near to bringing forth; (IAạr, Mṣb, Ḳ;) 
